1:31:38.333 --> 1:31:41.458
Do very well in school.

1:31:44.250 --> 1:31:47.500
That's the first thing I had to do.

1:31:51.625 --> 1:31:56.125
And sometimes that's all there is.

1:31:59.666 --> 1:32:01.166
I'm good at school.

1:32:01.250 --> 1:32:04.708
Yeah, if-if you do very well in school...

1:32:06.250 --> 1:32:07.541
...no one...

1:32:07.625 --> 1:32:10.083
Bet you write like nuns fuck.

1:32:19.375 --> 1:32:20.916
Where's this fucking chicken?

1:32:21.000 --> 1:32:23.541
Don't need any of
your mood swings after the day I had.

1:32:23.625 --> 1:32:25.791
What kind of fucking day
could you possibly have had?

1:32:25.875 --> 1:32:28.166
You out sucking cock
to pay for your goddamn chicken?

1:32:28.250 --> 1:32:30.250
-You know what, don't touch me!
-(thudding)

1:32:36.208 --> 1:32:37.833
Hey!

1:32:43.916 --> 1:32:47.541
Goddamn, you look like you had
some kind of a breakthrough.

1:32:49.375 --> 1:32:51.166
Like everything is...

1:32:52.750 --> 1:32:54.375
...falling into place.

1:32:54.458 --> 1:32:56.625
-Shut the fuck up.
-What did you say to me?

1:32:56.708 --> 1:32:59.041
I said shut the fuck up!

1:33:05.458 --> 1:33:07.708
You can't shut me up.

1:33:07.791 --> 1:33:10.000
I'm a broadcast professional.

1:33:12.041 --> 1:33:13.791
You weren't trying to shut me up

1:33:13.875 --> 1:33:15.916
when you were looking for me
on the radio dial.

1:33:16.000 --> 1:33:17.833
Fuck you.

1:33:17.916 --> 1:33:19.416
(The Voice exhales sharply)

1:33:19.500 --> 1:33:22.458
Man, you can't shut your daddy up.

1:33:22.541 --> 1:33:26.166
What are you gonna do
without the bad guy in your life?

1:33:26.250 --> 1:33:27.875
You're set.

1:33:29.791 --> 1:33:32.666
They'll all say that
you never had a chance.

1:33:43.791 --> 1:33:45.750
Where's your phone?

1:33:46.833 --> 1:33:49.458
("I Thought I Was a Child"
by Jackson Browne playing)

1:34:25.708 --> 1:34:27.708
(song continues over radio)

1:34:28.916 --> 1:34:30.750
Sorry about your father.

1:34:32.833 --> 1:34:34.500
He's not my father.

1:34:36.416 --> 1:34:38.208
You don't get to pick.

1:34:39.666 --> 1:34:41.041
Maybe.

1:34:44.333 --> 1:34:46.333
(dog barking in distance)

1:34:51.833 --> 1:34:53.458
Hi, honey.

1:34:55.375 --> 1:34:56.875
You're not gonna believe it.

1:34:56.958 --> 1:34:58.375
I got a great job.

1:34:58.458 --> 1:35:02.166
Your aunt, of all people, came through.

1:35:03.375 --> 1:35:05.333
It's in Westhampton. I got a desk.

1:35:05.416 --> 1:35:07.458
-Check the top?
-Yeah.

1:35:07.541 --> 1:35:10.250
They give you a book with a list
of phone numbers and addresses,

1:35:10.333 --> 1:35:14.333
and I talk to them about canceling
their whole life and getting term,

1:35:14.416 --> 1:35:18.291
putting the rest into an IRA
that builds tax-free.

1:35:19.333 --> 1:35:22.083
-How do I look?
-You look fantastic.

1:35:22.166 --> 1:35:24.166
Oh, God.

1:35:24.250 --> 1:35:27.083
I am gonna be late!

1:35:27.166 --> 1:35:30.458
They pay you a base salary, and then
you get a percentage of what you sell.

1:35:30.541 --> 1:35:32.125
There's some lasagna in the fridge.

1:35:32.208 --> 1:35:34.458
Leave some for Charlie.
Your grandpa already ate. I love you.

1:35:34.541 --> 1:35:35.625
-Okay.
-Wish me luck.

1:35:35.708 --> 1:35:37.916
-Good luck.
-(sighs)

1:35:38.000 --> 1:35:40.208
You sure this looks okay?

1:35:42.333 --> 1:35:44.333
Yeah. You look perfect.

1:35:46.625 --> 1:35:48.166
(chuckles)

1:35:52.541 --> 1:35:54.500
(chuckles softly)

1:35:54.583 --> 1:35:56.791
Your mother's settled, you know?

1:35:56.875 --> 1:35:58.416
Selling insurance.

1:35:58.500 --> 1:36:00.125
("Different Drum" by Stone Poneys playing)

1:36:00.208 --> 1:36:02.625
-Somebody's got to sell insurance, right?
-Yeah.

1:36:02.708 --> 1:36:05.375
Some of them are happy, probably.

1:36:05.458 --> 1:36:08.625
But I think Yale mostly took care
of her anxieties.

1:36:08.708 --> 1:36:10.125
(laughs)

1:36:10.208 --> 1:36:13.541
It's not my place to judge
what she's looking for, but...

1:36:13.625 --> 1:36:15.541
you know, I'd say she's all right.

1:36:15.625 --> 1:36:17.750
Yeah, hope so.

1:36:18.833 --> 1:36:20.708
What's all your stuff doing here?

1:36:21.708 --> 1:36:23.416
I'm going to Manhattan.

1:36:23.500 --> 1:36:25.625
It's time. Wesley has a place.

1:36:26.708 --> 1:36:29.083
Well, if you're gonna be a writer,
you got to get a job.

1:36:29.166 --> 1:36:31.666
Yeah. I'm not sure what that is yet.

1:36:32.666 --> 1:36:34.208
Insurance is taken.

1:36:34.291 --> 1:36:35.833
(chuckles)

1:36:37.041 --> 1:36:39.291
It's America. Pick something.

1:36:42.291 --> 1:36:43.541
That everything?

1:36:44.625 --> 1:36:46.083
Yeah, that's it.

1:36:46.166 --> 1:36:47.666
-(keys jingling)

1:36:51.833 --> 1:36:53.625
Don't say I never gave you nothing.

1:37:07.416 --> 1:37:09.166
(song stops)

1:37:14.625 --> 1:37:16.375
(sighs, chuckles softly)

1:37:34.333 --> 1:37:36.166
Whoa.

1:37:36.250 --> 1:37:38.375
-You got to be fucking kidding me.
-Whoa.

1:37:38.458 --> 1:37:40.625
You old enough to drive this thing?

1:37:40.708 --> 1:37:43.291
-- Better treat her with respect.
-- Steering wheel is on the left.

1:37:43.375 --> 1:37:44.583
It's a man's car.

1:37:44.666 --> 1:37:45.958
You sure there's gas in it?

1:37:46.041 --> 1:37:48.208
I guess you think you're a man now, huh?

1:37:48.291 --> 1:37:49.500
You little punk.

1:37:53.416 --> 1:37:56.083
-It's un-fucking-believable.
-(door opens)

1:37:56.166 --> 1:37:58.541
-Guy thinks he's Elvis Presley, you know?
-Kid's not a kid.

1:38:03.791 --> 1:38:05.208
You guys never gave me a car.

1:38:05.291 --> 1:38:07.166
Actually, he owes me this fucking car.

1:38:07.250 --> 1:38:09.041
(engine starts)

1:38:09.125 --> 1:38:11.625
("Do It Again" by Steely Dan playing)

1:38:13.958 --> 1:38:16.250
Get the fuck out of here.

1:38:16.333 --> 1:38:17.791
We don't want ya.

1:38:20.083 --> 1:38:22.000
-Scram!
-(laughter)

1:38:23.041 --> 1:38:24.375
Don't come back!

1:38:24.458 --> 1:38:26.125
(indistinct shouting)

1:38:29.541 --> 1:38:32.583
When you set out
to be a lawyer, you go to law school.

1:38:32.666 --> 1:38:34.416
You get a diploma for your effort.

1:38:34.500 --> 1:38:36.083
You pass the bar.

1:38:36.166 --> 1:38:39.791
In the text, it declares you
officially a lawyer.

1:38:39.875 --> 1:38:42.083
That's how most jobs work.

1:38:42.166 --> 1:38:44.666
But you're a writer
the minute you say you are.

1:38:44.750 --> 1:38:46.583
Nobody gives you a diploma.

1:38:46.666 --> 1:38:50.625
You have to prove it,
at least to yourself.

1:38:50.708 --> 1:38:53.916
On that day, driving to Manhattan--

1:38:54.000 --> 1:38:58.291
stashies in my wallet,
Uncle Charlie's car--

1:38:58.375 --> 1:39:00.833
that's the moment I knew I was a writer.

1:39:02.625 --> 1:39:06.375
And just my luck,
publishing was headed toward memoir.

1:43:37.500 --> 1:43:39.500
(song fades)

1:45:36.625 --> 1:45:38.625
(music ends)
